{"TopicId":186560,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"[New] Space Launch System / Orion Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-21T02:48:55Z","PageNum":37,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T09:22:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like a scam at this point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-03T13:10:19Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2020 01:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Wjolcz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T09:30:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd we are still years away from the flying article on a launchpad. I have no doubt price will only rise. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:angry:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_angry.png\u0022 title=\u0022:angry:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T12:23:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs unlikely these 146 megabux per engine will be turned into golden coins buried in the manufacturer\u0027s garden, but will be put in a bank and get reinvested, or at least will be paid in a diner or a barbershop, they are not really \u0022spent\u0022 but just \u0022alternatively reinvested\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they had sent the SLS/Orion to the Moon, these money would be just burnt and lost in space (literally).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, to make everybody happy, they should just appoint the SLS project to the status of official financial redistribution tool \u003Csub\u003E(can\u0027t think out a spelling for the SLS abbreviature, sorry)\u003C/sub\u003E and forget that stupid Moon \u003Csub\u003E(who really needs it? a bunch of nerds? they have KSP and are happy)\u003C/sub\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-03T12:26:07Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2020 12:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T13:53:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll that money is well spent to keep aerospace engineers out of trouble. If this program didn\u0027t keep their hands busy with polishing up old engines, they\u0027d be roaming the streets in prototype flying cars and personal drones, and generally menacing everyone.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Barzon","CreatedById":185383,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T14:39:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe contract is not purely for the engines. It includes tooling and development costs. From what I\u0027ve personally heard, the actual cost for an RS-25E is around 30 million.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T14:52:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588516744\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185383\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Barzon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Barzon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe contract is not purely for the engines. It includes tooling and development costs. From what I\u0027ve personally heard, the actual cost for an RS-25E is around 30 million.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey got 127 million each to refurb and improve the existing engines, including presumably dev (since the new engines will include the improvements).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey then got over a billion to retool, and produce 6 brand new engines. These are the first NEW engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re saying they are getting paid \u003Cem\u003Eagain\u003C/em\u003E to retool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I buy a part for my car, what matters is how much I pay them at the parts desk. Doesn\u0027t matter what it cost the mfg to come up with the design, all that matters is what I paid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt wouldn\u0027t matter, anyway, dev and tooling costs count. If the taxpayer writes a check, it\u0027s part of the cost.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe real cost of an SLS launch when the program is over will be: (total money spent on SLS)/launches\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the standard I will always use. Use it for Vulcan, use it for F9, use it for SS, NG, whatever. That is the real cost.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-03T14:53:11Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2020 02:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by tater\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flavio hc16","CreatedById":183153,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T17:37:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779969\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588517564\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey got 127 million each to refurb and improve the existing engines, including presumably dev (since the new engines will include the improvements).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey then got over a billion to retool, and produce 6 brand new engines. These are the first NEW engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re saying they are getting paid \u003Cem\u003Eagain\u003C/em\u003E to retool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I buy a part for my car, what matters is how much I pay them at the parts desk. Doesn\u0027t matter what it cost the mfg to come up with the design, all that matters is what I paid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt wouldn\u0027t matter, anyway, dev and tooling costs count. If the taxpayer writes a check, it\u0027s part of the cost.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe real cost of an SLS launch when the program is over will be: (total money spent on SLS)/launches\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the standard I will always use. Use it for Vulcan, use it for F9, use it for SS, NG, whatever. That is the real cost.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nman, if we include orion we might go at 10 billions/launch, with 5 launches\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T17:47:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust a hint for them: \u0022planned obsolescence\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T02:08:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9623023888\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/torybruno/status/1256962440790716416\u0022 style=\u0022height:345px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo a quarter of the price of the total launch service is the booster (SLS). Engines are 2/3 of that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0.165X = (146M*4)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nX=584/0.165\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nX=3.5 B$.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndustry rules of thumb. \u002B- by company, so the sort of company to always do things for minimal cost like Boeing might be substantially cheaper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n^Hat tip Eric Berger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T02:25:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223780240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588558109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso the sort of company to always do things for minimal cost like\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemind me again of which companies like to do things for maximal cost?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EchoLima","CreatedById":61992,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T02:26:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI get that SLS has unique capabilities as a\u00A0HLV, but this is ridiculous.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003EMoney burner go brrr\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T02:48:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223780243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588559107\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemind me again of which companies like to do things for maximal cost?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nALL.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey have a duty to, actually. It wasn\u0027t meant so much as a slam, but as a reaction to Bruno\u0027s claim that the norms would vary by company. I\u0027d expect that the SLS contractors at the very least meet Bruno\u0027s rule of thumb, it was more nailing down that SLS is likely not coming in below that value.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing that would result in reduced cost would be competition/bidding, and fixed price.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T07:12:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223780240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588558109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4704130090\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/torybruno/status/1256962440790716416\u0022 style=\u0022height:416px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo a quarter of the price of the total launch service is the booster (SLS). Engines are 2/3 of that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0.165X = (146M*4)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nX=584/0.165\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nX=3.5 B$.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndustry rules of thumb. \u002B- by company, so the sort of company to always do things for minimal cost like Boeing might be substantially cheaper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^Hat tip Eric Berger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou left off the cost of the SRBs.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T09:58:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4407209814\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/sciguyspace/status/1257135205174960128?s=21\u0022 style=\u0022height:498px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-04T10:44:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS Orion really is frighteningly expensive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf NASA cancelled SLS tomorrow and then went to NewSpace and said \u0022Here\u0027s SLS Orion\u0027s budget, get us to the moon by end of 2024.\u0022 I\u0027d bet on them to succeed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVulcan, New Glenn, Falcon Heavy, SuperHeavy, all boosters you can build a moon mission around that are more likely to be flying on a regular schedule by 2024 with a billion dollars dumped into them than SLS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhereas if you found twice SLS Orion\u0027s budget to give to Boeing I\u0027d still be 50:50 on them cocking it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-04T14:33:50Z\u0022 title=\u002205/04/2020 02:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 4, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EEmphasis\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-05T17:56:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223780314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588576343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/4/2020 at 1:12 AM, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou left off the cost of the SRBs.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I was trying to make SLS seem more reasonable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSRBs have got to be what, 50M$ each?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nICPS is ~175M$ I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n584\u002B100\u002B175= 859 M$. Minus the core stage itself. Assuming the RL-10 on ICPS is only 10M, the stage tank alone then costs 165M$. Fair guess that SLS core must cost at least 2X that. We\u0027ll even round down to 300M$. So total costs not counting any program costs whatsoever (which all count, divided by launches) is 1.159 B$. That\u0027s B1b. EUS has to be substantially more than ICPS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is also not counting Orion, which is north of a billion all by itself, and is currently literally the only payload for SLS. It is entirely fair to lump Orion in and treat this like Shuttle. Fixed program costs, plus marginal costs, divided by launches (per year). Program costs look to be similar, but flight rate looks to be 4X lower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Barzon","CreatedById":185383,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-05T18:20:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.sierralobo.com/sierra-lobo-inc-announces-nasas-artemis-human-landing-system-hls-award-on-dynetics-inc-team/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.sierralobo.com/sierra-lobo-inc-announces-nasas-artemis-human-landing-system-hls-award-on-dynetics-inc-team/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-06T19:55:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5608583591\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258121242743394307?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:936px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-06T21:04:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWooOOww. Eric really giving SLS both barrels here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9684186266\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258128324179701763?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:285px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9062466766\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258132534032044042?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:332px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6949307480\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258133370992803841?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:322px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7082667217\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258136948125904896?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:382px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1961698786\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258142849721393155?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:525px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3850912927\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258135430853263364?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:624px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4045135040\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258135765667786753?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:460px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah. Hard to disagree with a word.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-06T21:18:36Z\u0022 title=\u002205/06/2020 09:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 6, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-06T21:37:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223781593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588794951\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed381338245\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258121242743394307?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:1007px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn some bored moment a while back I calculated that if you stacked all the money spent on SLS in $100 bills, the top of the stack would be several times closer to the moon than the top of the planned rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EBonus points for anyone who confirms my calcs...\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-06T22:36:28Z\u0022 title=\u002205/06/2020 10:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 6, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Nightside\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-06T22:53:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3132780774\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258162141745631238?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:564px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo much opportunity cost to this boondoggle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SuperFastJellyfish","CreatedById":57985,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-07T04:41:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223781631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588801066\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn some bored moment a while back I calculated that if you stacked all the money spent on SLS in $100 bills, the top of the stack would be several times closer to the moon than the top of the planned rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EBonus points for anyone who confirms my calcs...\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA US federal reserve note is 0.11 mm thick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the end of the 2020 fiscal year, the SLS program will have cost \u003Ca href=\u0022https://oig.nasa.gov/docs/IG-20-012.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E$17 billion dollars-ish\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith no change in thickness via weight, the stack of benjamins would be 0.11 x 170,000,000 = 18.7 km\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe height of the initial SLS launch vehicle is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.lpi.usra.edu/lunar/constellation/SLS_FactSheet_long.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E0.09784 km\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe surface of the earth is 360,548 km from the moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n360,548 / 18.7 = 19,280.6\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n360,548 / 0.09784 = 3,685,077.7\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3,685,077.7 / 19,280.6 = 191.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the stack of benjamins would be ~191.1x closer to the moon than the top of the SLS launch vehicle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Space Nerd","CreatedById":198691,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-07T10:24:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223781615\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588799091\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWooOOww. Eric really giving SLS both barrels here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6943972442\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258128324179701763?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:253px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1652976022\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258132534032044042?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:275px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4250167568\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258133370992803841?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:293px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5925739786\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258136948125904896?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:291px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7572189842\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258142849721393155?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:370px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3671225363\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258135430853263364?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:398px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4402738719\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1258135765667786753?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:332px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah. Hard to disagree with a word.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t care about cost, I care about the KERBAL factor!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBesides, it can get us to the moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(With some help from the infrastructure of course.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-07T10:27:24Z\u0022 title=\u002205/07/2020 10:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Space Nerd\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-07T11:53:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223781810\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588847047\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198691\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Space Nerd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Space Nerd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t care about cost, I care about the KERBAL factor!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBesides, it can get us to the moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot by itself it can\u0027t. And you could buy \u003Cb\u003ESIX\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0FH partial reusable flights just for the cost of the *engines* (RS25, SRBs, RL10s) of SLS. Probably more than \u003Cstrong\u003EFIFTEEN\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EFH flights for the cost of one SLS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also Arianne, Atlas, Vulcan, H-IIB, Proton and Soyuz, all with respectable throw to TLI.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith some imaginative EOR and optionally international cooperation you can absolutely conduct a moon landing without SLS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Orion\u0027s just a capsule with extended life support and a beefy heat shield. There are plenty of other capsules a few upgrades away from handling trans lunar flight. It wouldn\u0027t take four years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027re completely spoiled at the moment for new hardware being developed rapidly. I consider the myth that it takes forever to get anything certified in space tech completely busted. Turns out it\u0027s just Boeing that doesn\u0027t have its act together.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-07T12:10:37Z\u0022 title=\u002205/07/2020 12:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-07T12:39:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223781836\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588852400\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd you could buy \u003Cb\u003ESIX\u003C/b\u003E\u00A0FH partial reusable flights just for the cost of the *engines* (RS25, SRBs, RL10s) of SLS. Probably more than \u003Cstrong\u003EFIFTEEN\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EFH flights for the cost of one SLS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MeanVillainousIchneumonfly-size_restrict\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022285\u0022 width=\u0022380\u0022 src=\u0022https://thumbs.gfycat.com/MeanVillainousIchneumonfly-size_restricted.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-07T22:43:25Z\u0022 title=\u002205/07/2020 10:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Wjolcz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}